alluxio.client.block.stream

Class PacketOutStream

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.io.OutputStream
      • alluxio.client.block.stream.PacketOutStream
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    BoundedStream, Cancelable, Closeable, Flushable, AutoCloseable

    @NotThreadSafe
public final class PacketOutStream
extends OutputStream
implements BoundedStream, Cancelable
    Provides an OutputStream implementation that is based on PacketWriter which streams data packet by packet.

      • cancel

        public void cancel()
            throws IOException
        Description copied from interface: Cancelable
        Cancels the write to Alluxio storage. This will delete all the temporary data and metadata that has been written to the worker(s). This method should be called when a write is aborted.
        Specified by:
        cancel in interface Cancelable
        Throws:
